# Auth bypass & route protection — Kite Hub

Whenever you create or modify a **page, layout, or API route handler** in this project, apply this checklist **before finishing**.

---

## 1. Classify the route

| Route type | Examples | Required protection |
|---|---|---|
| Public | `/kiosk`, `/api/kiosk/*`, `/api/jobs/*` | None (or own secret header) |
| Admin UI | `/admin/*` | `getAuthUser()` + role guard in layout |
| Admin API | `/api/admin/*` | `requireRole(["staff","admin"])` in handler |

---

## 2. Adding a new admin UI page

New admin pages **must** go under `src/app/admin/` — not under `src/app/(admin)/` (the route group used as source-of-truth pages). The `admin/` layout at `src/app/admin/layout.tsx` already provides session + role enforcement. You only need to create the page file; no extra auth code is required inside the page itself.

```
src/app/admin/
  layout.tsx          ← session + role guard (staff | admin)
  dashboard/page.tsx
  <new-section>/page.tsx   ← add here
```

Add the new link to `src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx` using the `/admin/<new-section>` href so navigation stays consistent.

---

## 3. Adding a new admin API route

Every Route Handler under `src/app/api/admin/` must call `requireRole` as its **first** async step:

```ts
// src/app/api/admin/<resource>/route.ts
import { requireRole } from "@/lib/auth";

export async function GET() {
  try {
    const actor = await requireRole(["staff", "admin"]);
    // ... handler logic using actor
  } catch (err) {
    return err as Response; // requireRole throws a NextResponse on failure
  }
}
```

Use `requireRole(["admin"])` for destructive or sensitive operations (DELETE, ban, etc.).

---

## 4. Dev auth bypass rules

- Bypass logic lives **only** in `src/lib/dev-bypass.ts`, `src/lib/auth0.ts`, and `src/lib/auth.ts`.
- **Never** add ad-hoc bypass logic (e.g., `if (process.env.NODE_ENV === "development") skip...`) inside pages or route handlers.
- `isDevAuthBypassEnabled()` already throws if `DEV_AUTH_BYPASS=true` outside `development`. Do not suppress or work around this.
- Do **not** import `dev-bypass.ts` in new client components.

---

## 5. Canonical URL convention

All admin routes use the `/admin/` prefix. No admin page should live at a top-level path like `/dashboard` without a redirect to `/admin/dashboard`.

- Sidebar hrefs: `/admin/<section>`
- Login `returnTo`: `/admin/dashboard`
- Post-login redirect in `src/app/page.tsx`: `/admin/dashboard`

---

## 6. Pre-release checklist (bypass removal)

Before deploying to production, verify:

- [ ] `DEV_AUTH_BYPASS` is **not** set in the production environment.
- [ ] `npm run check:no-bypass-prod` passes with exit code 0.
- [ ] Real Auth0 credentials (`AUTH0_DOMAIN`, `AUTH0_CLIENT_ID`, `AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET`, `AUTH0_BASE_URL`, `AUTH0_SECRET`) are configured.
- [ ] Login flow tested end-to-end with a real Auth0 user.
